Oh look! The thing went online again about an hour ago, for about half a minute.
Perhaps the panel just charged the battery long enough for 38 seconds of runtime. It took only a bit more than two hours to do so.
Guess what: Today it's cloudy. Therefore, I'm not sure if the (probably broken) solar panel manages to generate enough electricity at all.
Wait and see.
Update: I have installed the new panel, and now it seems to be working.
